Field.Label: Coverage
Field.HelpText: Coverage 1-Covers loss in value of the undamaged portion of the building due to demolition pursuant to a building ordinance or law. This is not a separate limit of insurance. Coverage 2-Demolition Cost covers the cost of demolishing and removing the debris of the undamaged portion of the building, if demolition is required by building ordinance or law. This is a separate limit of insurance. Coverage 3-Increased Cost of Construction covers the increased cost to repair, reconstruct or remodel damaged or undamaged parts of the building to comply with building ordinance or law, following damage to the building by a covered cause of loss. This is a separate limit of insurance, in excess of the $10,000 automatically provided under Additional Coverages section of the policy.
